  "SubGoals": [],
  "Description": "The TestMultipleHandlers goal utilizes caching to share state between different handlers and perform tests. It caches data for metrics and debug information for 10 minutes, calls the respective handlers on specified channels, and writes out specific messages to those channels. It then retrieves the cached data and checks for the presence of expected strings in the metrics and debug data. If the expected strings are not found, it throws an error indicating the test has failed. If both checks pass, it confirms that multiple handlers are functioning correctly.",
  "Visibility": 0,
